    "First, a small group of individuals is randomly selected from the population.",
    "These individuals are then compared based on their fitness scores, which measure how well they meet our optimization objectives (e.g., minimizing collision risk).",
    "The individual with the highest fitness score within this group is deemed the winner of the tournament and is selected for reproduction.",
    "This method ensures that individuals with higher fitness have a higher chance of being selected, yet it still allows for some diversity since the selection is random and not purely based on fitness.The crossover or recombination process is where selected individuals combine their genetic information to create children, which are then added to the next generation.",
